column10: [('Rated 2.0', 'RATED\\n  Visited this place after my first experience which was 2 years back and I absolutely loved this place. The food was amazing. But now, this restaurant has become very expensive and the food also was not good. The service was also pretty bad. Did not like the place at all now.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED\\n  The place is fabulous with great ambience. You have to checkout the veg sizzlers, Mali kofta and paneer Manchurian. Loaded with flavours and the sabji is always more for two folks.\\n\\nI am a little disappointed with the waiting time, but I feel good things comes go those who wait ;)'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED\\n  Food: 3\\nService 3\\nSans onions , garlic. To compensate for the lack of onions the dishes are spicy with an added dose of chilli. Hara bhara kebab was too dry. Pizza base was a tad too thick with a think layer of cheese. Sizzler was disappointing. Loaded with too much rice. Biryani was spicy but probably best of the lot. I guess we did try some offbeat items like pizza and sizzler. So I would give the benefit of doubt. column6: [('Rated 4.0', 'RATED\\n  Ambience- Big and spacious lawn was used to host new year event including unlimited food, drinks, dj, dholak performance, firedance and belly dance.\\n\\nPocket friendly- Reasonable for the services offered.\\n\\nFood- Veg and Non veg starters were served hot and had plenty of options including Fish and Chicken. The dishes could have been less oily.\\n\\nIn drinks you had plenty of options for alcoholic drinks but only 3 non alcoholic drinks which was dissapointing.\\n\\nMain course had good variety of Breads, Salads, Rice Items, Curries in both veg and nonveg. Desserts had plenty of options to choose from apart from the regular ones.\\n\\nService- Quick and prompt considering the crowd. The bar could have been better managed for non alcoholic section.\\n\\nRating- 4 for the awsome experience.')]

column2: 'RATED\\n  I was staying in this hotel and came down for the buffet breakfast they were serving in their cafe. The ambience was good to have any kind of meal. There were some window seats if we go and want to have a long and nice dinner. There were aisle seats in case we want a quick meal.\\n\\nThe staff were courteous and were serving us promptly. The buffet spread was not too big but decent and covered few and missed few.\\n\\nThe buffet contained aloo parathas which were very tasty. The noodles was very oily. The potato cubes were absolutely lip smacking. The poori bhaji was good too. The wadas were very crispy and soft and went well with the chutney.\\n\\nI ordered for a spicy egg dosa and a cheese omelet. The cheese omlet was out of the world. I instantly fell in love with it. Comes with 2 large jowar rotis, good serving of rice, unlimited sambhar, baingan subzi and dal. Now this food is north Karnataka style. Predominantly rai flavor. Healthy low oil and flavorful. The dal was very healthy moong chana combo. Sambhar had lots of fresh veggies. Alo there was curds onions 3 chutnies tomato, groundnut and a dry podi. Jowar is a millet category of grains no gluten and far superior to wheat in nutrition\\n\\nSERVICE\\nQuick attentive friendly\\n\\nOVERALL A MUST TRY. Chai ,\\n4 .jalebi\\n\\nWould like to taste daal baati once. \\n\\nWould rate 4 out of 5.\\nFood taste : 4.5/5\\nAmbiance : 2 /5\\nVariety : 3/5\\nPocket friendly : Yes\\nservice : 4/5 \\n\\nIt is a daily eat place ,It is not high restaurant for a big treat or something. \\nBut it beats many big restaurants as far as good taste is concerned.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED\\n  As hunger fangs started to take full affect on Friday noon for lunch; me and my colleagues decided to head out of office campus to try a new joint in neighborhood and this time it happened to be a Rajasthani cuisine restaurant named Ramdev Bhojnalaya.\\n\\nIn terms of demography it is located on the street which has Malabar hotel; just a little further on the same road.\\n\\nWe ordered for a Masala Papad (Sabudana), and 3 plates of Roti Subzi which consisted of Dal, a gravy subzi and 4 rotis. Have to admit it is simplicious ;)\\n\\nService is very normal as it is a small joint.\\n\\nA perfect value for money as meal for two would cost less than Rs 150/-\\n\\nDefinitely Recommended\\n\\nOverall Rating:\\n\\nAmbiance: 3.5/5\\n\\nFood: 4.5/5\\n\\nTaste: 4.5/5\\n\\nService: 4/5\\n\\nValue: 4/5\\n\\nankurkacker.wordpress.com'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED\\n  Homely food...\\nIf you are staying away from home and want to give a change from typical spicy food.\\nPlz give a try to Ramdev bhojnalaya. ...')]
